Dialogue: 0,1:11:33.14,1:11:33.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Never learned to spot it, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:33.85,1:11:34.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, it goes on the same.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:34.39,1:11:34.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that all it did?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:34.96,1:11:45.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and pluck your tongue. Isn't that awful? Like getting old. Wrinkles. Like fading vision.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:45.78,1:11:59.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Like sore feet. Get used to it. Okay, the next. The next, the next. Levels of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:11:59.36,1:12:05.06,Default,,0,0,0,,and rate of happiness. Again, you see, trying to put causality as something outside of yourself
Dialogue: 0,1:12:05.06,1:12:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,is the denial of the truth. Because rate of happiness is an inner decision. Inner decision.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:12.00,1:12:17.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And we see that the rate of happiness here is exactly correlated with the calibrated
Dialogue: 0,1:12:17.80,1:12:25.42,Default,,0,0,0,,level of consciousness. Below 200, very little is going to make anybody happy. No matter
Dialogue: 0,1:12:25.42,1:12:33.65,Default,,0,0,0,,how you vote. No matter what you do for them. Because happiness is something they've rejected
Dialogue: 0,1:12:33.65,1:12:37.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and would rather hang on to guilt, grief, fear, desire, anger, and fear. And that's
Dialogue: 0,1:12:37.57,1:12:45.10,Default,,0,0,0,,anger, pride, hostility, and hatred. Huh? That is more dear to them. You see how disappointed
Dialogue: 0,1:12:45.10,1:12:50.67,Default,,0,0,0,,people are. When somebody's accused of something guilty, and then they find out that it was
Dialogue: 0,1:12:50.67,1:12:56.72,Default,,0,0,0,,innocent. People are disappointed as all get out. See that in politics all the time.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:56.72,1:13:01.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Try and make them out to be, yeah. And then when they find out it was accidental, everybody's
Dialogue: 0,1:13:01.89,1:13:07.06,Default,,0,0,0,,disappointed. Oh, I thought we had somebody else we could hate.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:07.06,1:13:08.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:08.06,1:13:16.72,Default,,0,0,0,,The rate of happiness. So one purpose then, in self-improvement and spiritual work, is
Dialogue: 0,1:13:16.72,1:13:24.23,Default,,0,0,0,,that the inner state of happiness rises. It doesn't mean that a passing emotionality can't
Dialogue: 0,1:13:24.23,1:13:30.57,Default,,0,0,0,,drop to here. But that's a passing emotionality. That's not who you are. Happiness is who you
Dialogue: 0,1:13:30.57,1:13:39.15,Default,,0,0,0,,are. Who you are. After somebody runs into your new car, you're going to say, oh, darn
Dialogue: 0,1:13:39.15,1:13:39.96,Default,,0,0,0,,it. Oh, darn it.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:40.02,1:13:45.43,Default,,0,0,0,,but who you are isn't really affected you know you were who you are before you
Dialogue: 0,1:13:45.43,1:13:50.48,Default,,0,0,0,,had that car view you are long after you get rid of that car who you are is not
Dialogue: 0,1:13:50.48,1:13:58.39,Default,,0,0,0,,affected these people here this is who they are this is who they are and given
Dialogue: 0,1:13:58.39,1:14:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,an opportunity for peace they spit upon it spit upon it spit upon it they don't
Dialogue: 0,1:14:08.00,1:14:16.57,Default,,0,0,0,,just not adopt it they get up and denounce denounce it okay we'll move on
Dialogue: 0,1:14:16.57,1:14:22.42,Default,,0,0,0,,it's so they've decided on who they are so happiness is a consequence of who you
Dialogue: 0,1:14:22.42,1:14:28.69,Default,,0,0,0,,are we'll be talking more about this because of some things we need to know
Dialogue: 0,1:14:28.69,1:14:33.89,Default,,0,0,0,,not only in this lifetime but for a long time identification a spiritual truth
Dialogue: 0,1:14:33.89,1:14:38.47,Default,,0,0,0,,etc on teachings then we're going to be doing
Dialogue: 0,1:14:38.47,1:14:39.72,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrations of
Dialogue: 0,1:14:39.72,1:14:39.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Validation for You
Dialogue: 0,1:14:39.82,1:14:41.86,Default,,0,0,0,,various spiritual practices and things.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:42.48,1:14:44.68,Default,,0,0,0,,But this is what we need to know.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:46.00,1:14:48.42,Default,,0,0,0,,A spiritual truth has a universality.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:49.43,1:14:50.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Truth is always the same,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:51.44,1:14:56.97,Default,,0,0,0,,whether it was the great sages of ancient India,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:56.97,1:15:00.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Aryan culture, about 5,000 B.C.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:01.23,1:15:05.78,Default,,0,0,0,,The Gitas calibrate in the 900s.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:06.80,1:15:09.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So that was universally true.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:09.30,1:15:10.88,Default,,0,0,0,,India's on the other side of the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:10.88,1:15:15.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And the time difference is many thousands of years.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:16.11,1:15:18.80,Default,,0,0,0,,At 5,000 years on the other side of the world,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:19.47,1:15:21.47,Default,,0,0,0,,the same truth of the enlightened sage
Dialogue: 0,1:15:21.47,1:15:25.02,Default,,0,0,0,,is the same as the truth of the enlightened sage today
Dialogue: 0,1:15:25.02,1:15:26.18,Default,,0,0,0,,in this country here.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:27.23,1:15:28.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Truth is all-inclusive.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:28.93,1:15:30.10,Default,,0,0,0,,It's non-sectarian.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:30.26,1:15:31.23,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't belong to anybody.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:31.97,1:15:33.10,Default,,0,0,0,,It's open to all.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:33.85,1:15:35.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Truth is free.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:36.80,1:15:37.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Integrity of purpose.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:38.14,1:15:39.52,Default,,0,0,0,,There's nothing to gain or lose.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:40.43,1:15:41.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Non-sectarian.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:41.97,1:15:44.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Truth is not the exposition of a limitation
Dialogue: 0,1:15:44.27,1:15:46.85,Default,,0,0,0,,that only us people have the truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:47.10,1:15:49.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, that's one of the biggest problems in the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:49.90,1:15:51.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Only us people have the truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:51.71,1:15:54.89,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no way they can prove that they have the truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:55.94,1:15:58.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Other than calibrating levels of consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:58.85,1:16:01.67,Default,,0,0,0,,mankind has never had any way of discerning truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:02.36,1:16:05.13,Default,,0,0,0,,People who are advanced begin to intuit it.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:05.93,1:16:08.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And they see that if a prevailing understanding
Dialogue: 0,1:16:08.10,1:16:09.75,Default,,0,0,0,,has prevailed for thousands of years,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:09.90,1:16:11.22,Default,,0,0,0,,that there's a likelihood to it.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:11.60,1:16:14.72,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, the Native American people calibrated very high.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:15.64,1:16:19.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Their spirituality, they didn't have any gurus.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:20.01,1:16:25.73,Default,,0,0,0,,There was no great savior, no guru, no Buddha, no prophet.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:28.02,1:16:30.77,Default,,0,0,0,,The Native American people intuited great spirit.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:32.21,1:16:33.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And then they intuited.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:34.73,1:16:37.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And then they began to see, they understand animal spirits.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:39.00,1:16:43.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Because what they were seeing was the energy field
Dialogue: 0,1:16:43.27,1:16:44.22,Default,,0,0,0,,that all of us have.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:44.22,1:16:51.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And all doggies come out of one prevailing attractor field.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:51.25,1:16:53.31,Default,,0,0,0,,So they didn't know anything about non-linear dynamics
Dialogue: 0,1:16:53.31,1:16:54.17,Default,,0,0,0,,or attractor fields.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:54.81,1:16:59.25,Default,,0,0,0,,But you see the paradigm out of which all kitties behave like kitties,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:59.44,1:17:01.55,Default,,0,0,0,,there's just one attractor field of kittiness.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:02.78,1:17:04.40,Default,,0,0,0,,There's one attractor field of dogginess.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:04.60,1:17:06.48,Default,,0,0,0,,There's one attractor field for being a lion.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:07.48,1:17:11.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And all lions out there are connected with this attractor field
Dialogue: 0,1:17:11.27,1:17:15.59,Default,,0,0,0,,in which everything known within the lion has been stored forever.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:15.85,1:17:18.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't that interesting?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:19.05,1:17:21.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Native American people intuited that.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:21.72,1:17:24.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So they would pray to the spirit of the lion
Dialogue: 0,1:17:24.44,1:17:26.28,Default,,0,0,0,,before they went into the jungle.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:27.84,1:17:29.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I would like a friendly spirit of the lion
Dialogue: 0,1:17:29.76,1:17:30.97,Default,,0,0,0,,if I was in the jungle.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:33.68,1:17:34.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Make a sacrifice.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:35.76,1:17:38.06,Default,,0,0,0,,But you see the devotion, apologizing,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:38.50,1:17:40.27,Default,,0,0,0,,apologizing to kill the deer.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:41.07,1:17:43.60,Default,,0,0,0,,You apologize that you need to take this food.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:43.60,1:17:46.53,Default,,0,0,0,,At the same time, the deer's spiritual evolution,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:46.56,1:17:51.56,Default,,0,0,0,,is advanced because each being becomes,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:51.56,1:17:54.52,Default,,0,0,0,,by its sacrifice, it earns the karmic right
Dialogue: 0,1:17:54.52,1:17:57.18,Default,,0,0,0,,to become that which is beyond it.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:57.18,1:18:02.46,Default,,0,0,0,,By its sacrifice, I give my life to thee, O Lord.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:02.46,1:18:05.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And by that, do I earn the right to evolve.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:05.60,1:18:08.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So you see, the evolution of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:18:08.64,1:18:10.18,Default,,0,0,0,,has been earned in the Bhagavad,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:10.18,1:18:16.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, what should we call it, Gita?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:16.53,1:18:22.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Can't tell one Gita from another, y'all.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:22.60,1:18:23.63,Default,,0,0,0,,One, nine, 10.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:23.78,1:18:25.80,Default,,0,0,0,,What are the great Gitas?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:25.80,1:18:28.31,Default,,0,0,0,,What time do we close this morning?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:28.31,1:18:29.15,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:29.15,1:18:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:30.00,1:18:32.07,Default,,0,0,0,,What time do we stop?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:32.07,1:18:33.39,Default,,0,0,0,,1115.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:33.39,1:18:35.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it 1115?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:35.76,1:18:38.59,Default,,0,0,0,,In America?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:38.59,1:18:41.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't believe it, let me say this.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:41.97,1:18:45.43,Default,,0,0,0,,It says 1115.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:45.43,1:18:47.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:47.38,1:18:49.30,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not sectarian, devoid of positionality,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:49.30,1:18:51.68,Default,,0,0,0,,no new karma, so no.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:51.68,1:18:53.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Doesn't demand anything from the students,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:53.14,1:18:54.57,Default,,0,0,0,,free of force or intimidation.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:54.57,1:18:56.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Quick, the next one.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:56.43,1:18:58.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Not finding freedom, come on.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:58.55,1:19:00.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Inspirational.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:00.13,1:19:01.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Non-materialistic.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:01.21,1:19:02.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Detached.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:02.75,1:19:04.48,Default,,0,0,0,,If you listen, it's your problem.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:04.48,1:19:07.25,Default,,0,0,0,,If you don't listen, it's your problem.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:07.25,1:19:10.22,Default,,0,0,0,,It's benign, it doesn't want to beat anybody up.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:10.22,1:19:12.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's non-dualistic.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:12.85,1:19:16.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And it stems from tranquility and police.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:16.31,1:19:17.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Peace.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:20.50,1:19:22.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Tranquility and the police, idiot.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:24.88,1:19:44.32,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll stop here.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:44.32,1:19:45.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Tardy, tardy, tardy.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:54.35,1:20:00.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody, okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:00.68,1:20:02.18,Default,,0,0,0,,We ended up talking about teachers,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:02.18,1:20:06.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and we're really gonna be,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:06.35,1:20:09.35,Default,,0,0,0,,we're gonna end up talking about subjective reality,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:09.35,1:20:11.38,Default,,0,0,0,,experiential reality.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:11.38,1:20:12.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I just wanted to cover the background
Dialogue: 0,1:20:12.89,1:20:16.14,Default,,0,0,0,,for people that are new, for the theoretical.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:16.14,1:20:19.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And as you hear it over and over again,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:19.35,1:20:22.43,Default,,0,0,0,,it becomes incorporated,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:22.43,1:20:23.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and you begin to see things,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:23.92,1:20:28.18,Default,,0,0,0,,it assists the evolution of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:28.18,1:20:29.36,Default,,0,0,0,,What was the last slide?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:29.36,1:20:31.47,Default,,0,0,0,,We had to do with the integrous teachers
Dialogue: 0,1:20:31.47,1:20:33.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and all the teachings.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:33.02,1:20:37.47,Default,,0,0,0,,And one thing that dawned on me this morning was,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:37.60,1:20:41.96,Default,,0,0,0,,religions and spiritual teachers
Dialogue: 0,1:20:46.06,1:20:49.19,Default,,0,0,0,,put demands and obligations and pledges
Dialogue: 0,1:20:49.19,1:20:52.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and God knows what on the students.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:52.46,1:20:56.26,Default,,0,0,0,,But you never hear the teacher make a statement
Dialogue: 0,1:20:56.26,1:21:04.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and a pledge of what is his responsibility to the student.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:04.30,1:21:07.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Forget about the student's obligation to the teacher.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:07.03,1:21:08.97,Default,,0,0,0,,But the teacher's obligation,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:08.97,1:21:12.03,Default,,0,0,0,,the teacher should make a statement of commitment.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:12.03,1:21:14.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Commitment to what?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:14.57,1:21:17.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Commitment to integrity.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:17.84,1:21:21.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Commitment to not exploit the students.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:21.93,1:21:24.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:24.06,1:21:26.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And you see the ravages that have occurred
Dialogue: 0,1:21:26.76,1:21:30.52,Default,,0,0,0,,in some of the world's most major religions
Dialogue: 0,1:21:30.52,1:21:31.88,Default,,0,0,0,,for a lack of integrity
Dialogue: 0,1:21:31.88,1:21:35.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and a statement of commitment of the teacher.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:37.55,1:21:39.55,Default,,0,0,0,,The teacher should first make a statement
Dialogue: 0,1:21:39.55,1:21:42.17,Default,,0,0,0,,that I'm committed to you.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:42.17,1:21:45.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm committed to the highest truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:45.30,1:21:47.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And I also make the commitment not to exploit
Dialogue: 0,1:21:47.96,1:21:48.98,Default,,0,0,0,,the,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:48.98,1:21:51.36,Default,,0,0,0,,student-teacher relationship,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:53.13,1:21:56.15,Default,,0,0,0,,the prevalence of fallen
Dialogue: 0,1:21:56.15,1:21:57.97,Default,,0,0,0,,gurus is increasing.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:58.50,1:22:00.06,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, we weren't even allowed to use
Dialogue: 0,1:22:00.06,1:22:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the word in the last couple of books.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:03.22,1:22:04.35,Default,,0,0,0,,We asked if we used the word,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:04.46,1:22:04.93,Default,,0,0,0,,it said no.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:06.77,1:22:08.56,Default,,0,0,0,,The meaning of the word is meant to
Dialogue: 0,1:22:08.56,1:22:11.03,Default,,0,0,0,,exploit it, to exploit
Dialogue: 0,1:22:11.03,1:22:13.26,Default,,0,0,0,,the student for money,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:13.39,1:22:15.38,Default,,0,0,0,,power, sex, control, God knows
Dialogue: 0,1:22:15.38,1:22:17.64,Default,,0,0,0,,what. I think a teacher
Dialogue: 0,1:22:17.64,1:22:19.80,Default,,0,0,0,,should stand up and make a declaration
Dialogue: 0,1:22:19.80,1:22:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,of intention and commitment
Dialogue: 0,1:22:22.00,1:22:22.88,Default,,0,0,0,,to the student,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:23.86,1:22:25.35,Default,,0,0,0,,not just vice versa.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:29.09,1:22:38.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I've run across fallen gurus
Dialogue: 0,1:22:38.06,1:22:40.11,Default,,0,0,0,,in my lifetime, and I can
Dialogue: 0,1:22:40.11,1:22:42.07,Default,,0,0,0,,see what the pitfalls are, and I can see
Dialogue: 0,1:22:42.07,1:22:42.89,Default,,0,0,0,,how easy it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:43.73,1:22:45.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, in our own lectures,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:45.81,1:22:48.22,Default,,0,0,0,,especially the calibration levels of the 500s,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:48.92,1:22:50.19,Default,,0,0,0,,we try to warn
Dialogue: 0,1:22:50.19,1:22:51.69,Default,,0,0,0,,people of the downside
Dialogue: 0,1:22:51.69,1:22:54.03,Default,,0,0,0,,as you get
Dialogue: 0,1:22:54.03,1:22:56.07,Default,,0,0,0,,into the 500s, and especially
Dialogue: 0,1:22:56.07,1:22:57.30,Default,,0,0,0,,the high 500s,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:57.73,1:22:59.97,Default,,0,0,0,,which is where most of the famous
Dialogue: 0,1:22:59.97,1:23:01.96,Default,,0,0,0,,gurus of the last
Dialogue: 0,1:23:01.96,1:23:03.80,Default,,0,0,0,,decade have gotten to before
Dialogue: 0,1:23:03.80,1:23:04.34,Default,,0,0,0,,they fell.
